cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with complexity theory and graph theory, specifically the Khot's 2 to 2 games conjecture and the non-expanding sets in the shortcode and Grassman graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial and geometric arguments, suggesting possible sub-categories of cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
